This paper is about dialogue state tracking using neural networks, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of end-to-end trainable neural networks, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions candidate-generation-based approaches, which could fall under the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SD) as it involves designing and implementing algorithms. Finally, the paper uses a hybrid approach to improve performance, which could fall under the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) as it involves combining different techniques to optimize performance.
